## Project Overview

This project implements a computer vision system to detect whether a cricket ball made contact with the bat during a delivery. It is designed as an accessible alternative to commercial thermal-imaging systems (e.g., Hot Spot), using only standard video footage and classical image processing techniques.

The system takes a short video clip as input, allows the user to draw a Region of Interest (ROI) around the bat, and produces an annotated output video that labels each frame as **CONTACT** or **NO CONTACT**, with a red motion-highlight overlay on the bat region.

---

## Problem Statement

Cricket umpires often need to determine whether the ball grazed the bat edge — a judgment critical for dismissals (caught behind, LBW reviews, etc.). The current gold standard, **Hot Spot**, relies on expensive thermal cameras ($50,000+ per system) that are not available at most levels of the game. Manual umpire decisions remain error-prone.

This project proposes a cost-effective, purely software-based solution using standard broadcast or recorded video.

---

## Image Processing Pipeline

The detection pipeline consists of five sequential stages:

```
Video Input
    │
    ▼
1. Frame Extraction
   └─ Read video at native FPS using OpenCV
   └─ Store frames as NumPy arrays

    │
    ▼
2. Preprocessing
   └─ Convert to grayscale (cv2.cvtColor)
   └─ Apply Gaussian blur for noise reduction (cv2.GaussianBlur)

    │
    ▼
3. ROI Selection (Bat Region)
   └─ User draws bounding box on first frame (cv2.selectROI)
   └─ All further analysis is restricted to this region
   └─ Reduces false positives from background motion

    │
    ▼
4. Frame Differencing + Morphological Filtering
   └─ Compute absolute difference between consecutive frames (cv2.absdiff)
   └─ Threshold the difference image (cv2.threshold)
   └─ Apply morphological opening to remove noise (cv2.morphologyEx)
   └─ Dilate to strengthen true-positive regions (cv2.dilate)

    │
    ▼
5. Contact Decision + Visualization
   └─ Count non-zero pixels in cleaned difference image
   └─ Label frame CONTACT if pixel count > min_contact_pixels
   └─ Overlay red mask on motion region
   └─ Write annotated frame to output video
```

### Techniques Used

| Category | Technique | OpenCV Function |
|----------|-----------|-----------------|
| Basic | Grayscale conversion | `cv2.cvtColor` |
| Basic | Gaussian blur | `cv2.GaussianBlur` |
| Basic | Frame differencing | `cv2.absdiff` |
| Basic | Binary thresholding | `cv2.threshold` |
| Intermediate | Morphological opening | `cv2.morphologyEx` |
| Intermediate | Dilation | `cv2.dilate` |
| Intermediate | ROI-based analysis | `cv2.selectROI` |
| Advanced | Contour detection *(pipeline extension)* | `cv2.findContours` |
| Advanced | Canny edge detection *(pipeline extension)* | `cv2.Canny` |

